pondering whether I can use a Jersey Application subclass from the library, but it seems like that might not work. Instead, a custom HttpServlet might be better, although I'm concerned about the native failure unless the class literal for c.newInstance is transformed automatically. It seems the native image can see calls to GrizzlyWebContainerFactory.create. I wonder if the parameter constant can help register that constructor because often, the native image can resolve Class.newInstance calls when the Class object is constant.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_PbG7EUTY1rtsHlzsbuvAF7TR|fc_0e19b66bb74e824f016a4128d73cb481909a91e20fe63ab18f", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.sun.jersey/jersey-grizzly2/1.9/src/test/java/com_sun_jersey/jersey_grizzly2/GrizzlyWebContainerFactoryTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        Map<String, String> initParams = Map.of(\n                ClassNamesResourceConfig.PROPERTY_CLASSNAMES, HelloResource.class.getName());", "newText": "        Map<String, String> initParams = Map.of(\n                \"com.sun.jersey.config.property.resourceConfigClass\",\n                ClassNamesResourceConfig.class.getName(),\n                ClassNamesResourceConfig.PROPERTY_CLASSNAMES,\n                HelloResource.class.getName());"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 332, "output": 1190, "cacheRead": 58368, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59890, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782655172454, "responseId": "resp_0e19b66bb74e824f016a4128c5336c8190b7c0c79411096e57"}}
